{
  "page": "Corlos",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Corlos</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Corlos.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Corlos.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/19/Corlos.png/350px-Corlos.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"442\" srcset=\"/images/1/19/Corlos.png 1.5x\" /></a><div>Corlos as depicted in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>: Histories &amp; Lore.</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nCorlos son of Caster</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Lord of Casterly Rock\">Lord of Casterly Rock</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Casterly\" title=\"House Casterly\">House Casterly</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dawn_Age\" title=\"Dawn Age\">Dawn Age</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Caster\" title=\"Caster\">Caster</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Corlos</b> is a figure from the <a href=\"/index.php/Dawn_Age\" title=\"Dawn Age\">Dawn Age</a> and the founder of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Casterly\" title=\"House Casterly\">House Casterly</a>. His father's name was <a href=\"/index.php/Caster\" title=\"Caster\">Caster</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Corlos&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>According to legend, Corlos was a <a href=\"/index.php/Huntsman\" title=\"Huntsman\">huntsman</a> who lived in a village near to where <a href=\"/index.php/Lannisport\" title=\"Lannisport\">Lannisport</a> would eventually stand. When a <a href=\"/index.php/Lion\" title=\"Lion\">lion</a> began preying on the village's sheep, Corlos tracked it back to its den, a cave in the base of <a href=\"/index.php/The_Rock\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Rock\">the Rock</a>. Armed with only a <a href=\"/index.php/Spear\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Spear\">spear</a>, he slew the lion and his mate, but spared the newborn cubs. This act of mercy so pleased the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_gods\" title=\"Old gods\">old gods</a> that they sent a sudden ray of sunlight deep into the cave, revealing the gleam of yellow <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> in a vein as thick as a man's waist.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a> believes Corlos soon moved inside the cave and fortified its entrance and as centuries passed, his descendants delved deeper and deeper into the earth to mine the gold but also carving halls, galleries and tunnels, transforming the gigantic Rock into a castle that dwarfed every other seat in <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Corlos&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Seven Kingdoms&#58; The Westerlands.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"wikitable succession-box noprint\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:small;clear:both;\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b>New title</b>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 40%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b>1st<br /> <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Lord of Casterly Rock\">Lord of Casterly Rock</a> </b>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b>Unknown</b><div style=\"font-size:90%\">Next known title holder:</div><b><a href=\"/index.php/Loren_I_Lannister\" title=\"Loren I Lannister\">Loren I Lannister</a> </b>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403125037\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.072 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.257 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 798/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 12693/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 5323/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 724/2097152 b